06:12.166 --> 06:15.499
Word is it's turning into
a hell of a war over there, Captain.

06:15.628 --> 06:20.788
We're going there, pal.
When we're in 'Nam, we're in Combat City.

06:20.925 --> 06:24.341
I am ready. Really ready.

06:25.805 --> 06:28.841
I'll pop some rounds with you. Marine!

06:30.392 --> 06:35.101
- How's Vi taken to your leaving?
- I think she hates everything military.

06:35.231 --> 06:39.275
But she stands behind me.
She knows I want it more than anything.

06:39.401 --> 06:42.237
- How about Sally?
- She's OK.

06:42.363 --> 06:46.989
I don't think she really understands it all,
but she accepts it.

06:48.077 --> 06:51.197
You can't ask
for a helluva lot more than that.

06:53.958 --> 06:58.833
<i>An American spokesman reported</i>
<i>rockets, artillery and mortar fire...</i>

06:58.963 --> 07:01.667
- Jeez!
- Remember Jim Hanson?

07:02.883 --> 07:07.130
He got blown away
in the middle of the street right in Saigon.

07:07.263 --> 07:12.304
That's an embarrassment.
Makes us look like the goddamn B Team.

07:12.434 --> 07:16.266
Word is from on top that Charlie
shot his wad with this Tet Offensive

07:16.397 --> 07:19.481
and it's just a matter of a mop-up time.

07:19.608 --> 07:22.977
I've waited a long time
for an opportunity like this.

07:23.112 --> 07:25.270
You're gonna make major.

07:26.615 --> 07:28.240
- Major?
- Major.

07:28.367 --> 07:34.655
Major and Mrs Robert Hyde? I'll have
to get my skirts lengthened for that one.

07:34.790 --> 07:36.830
Start wearing girdles.

07:36.959 --> 07:42.250
- You'll have to watch your language.
- Right. Very reserved.

07:43.340 --> 07:47.883
I'm actually excited.
I never thought it would get like this.

07:48.012 --> 07:54.513
I have competitive nervousness.
I feel like I'm off to the Olympic Games.

07:54.643 --> 07:56.683
Bob is very sexy.

07:56.812 --> 07:59.386
In 13 months I'll throw you
the damnedest party.

07:59.523 --> 08:02.809
We'll have a side of beef,
a case of Jack Daniels,

08:02.943 --> 08:05.980
and maybe I'll even get you
a couple of congressmen.

08:06.113 --> 08:07.691
Fantastic.

08:07.823 --> 08:10.907
- I'll bring you back a souvenir.
- Like what?

08:11.035 --> 08:13.822
A Commie AK-47.

08:13.954 --> 08:17.323
- Robert? Sorry to interrupt.
- Mrs Vickery.

08:17.458 --> 08:20.127
I wanted to pass on
the Colonel's best wishes.

08:20.252 --> 08:24.748
- Isn't he able to come by later?
- No. Tonight's his chess night.

08:24.882 --> 08:29.674
- Sally, be sure to keep in touch.
- I will, Mrs Vickery.

08:29.803 --> 08:32.472
- She'll be staying with my mom.
- Oh, nice.

08:32.597 --> 08:36.049
Earl, your Kathy's doing
a wonderful job on the paper.

08:36.184 --> 08:40.811
- Don't let it go to your head, young lady.
- I've got a lot of good ideas.

08:40.940 --> 08:42.979
Call me tomorrow.

08:44.526 --> 08:47.693
- May God be with you, Robert.
- Thank you, Mrs Vickery.

08:51.408 --> 08:53.448
That was very nice.

08:53.577 --> 08:57.160
<i>A time of innocence</i>

08:57.289 --> 09:02.117
<i>A time of confidences</i>

09:02.253 --> 09:05.752
<i>Long ago it must be</i>

09:05.881 --> 09:08.882
<i>I have a photograph</i>

09:09.009 --> 09:11.085
<i>Preserve your memories</i>...

09:11.220 --> 09:13.509
Now hear this!

09:14.598 --> 09:20.304
It is exactly zero hour minus six.

09:20.437 --> 09:24.221
Your orders for the day are:

09:24.358 --> 09:29.518
Go directly to the bedroom.

09:31.198 --> 09:34.947
Do not pass "Go".

09:35.077 --> 09:39.122
Do not collect dinner.

09:40.624 --> 09:44.040
- Aren't you hungry?
- Well...

09:44.169 --> 09:47.455
Does a bear make big potty in the woods?

09:49.883 --> 09:54.592
From the Halls of Montezuma
to the shores of Tripoli...

09:58.058 --> 10:00.596
I will fight...

10:02.396 --> 10:05.480
my country's battles...

10:07.568 --> 10:10.403
on land,

10:10.529 --> 10:12.652
in the air...

10:33.761 --> 10:35.800
Bob?

10:39.350 --> 10:41.556
What are you doing?

10:41.685 --> 10:44.770
This darn thing wouldn't pop up.

10:46.190 --> 10:50.437
You never know
when you're gonna want some toast.

11:00.954 --> 11:03.410
I gotta start getting ready.

11:04.792 --> 11:08.243
You don't need to be afraid
for me, you know.

11:09.797 --> 11:12.003
I <i>am</i> afraid.

11:13.842 --> 11:16.084
But I'm proud of you.

11:16.220 --> 11:20.134
There was nothing I could do
here in California.

11:20.265 --> 11:22.305
I know.

11:23.977 --> 11:28.390
That's where I belong. And I am a Marine.

11:31.610 --> 11:35.109
I gotta go. Pay the bar bill.

11:35.239 --> 11:38.904
And let's get the generator
in this thing fixed.

11:39.034 --> 11:42.118
And call my mom and let her know
when you're coming.

11:42.246 --> 11:46.908
- I bought you a present, sweetheart.
- I don't have anything for you.

11:54.091 --> 11:57.590
Oh, Sally. It's a little wedding ring.

12:00.639 --> 12:04.553
Look how outstanding that is. Huh?

12:04.685 --> 12:06.724
I like it.

12:08.480 --> 12:13.226
- You'll probably take it off on liberty.
- No way.

12:13.360 --> 12:16.776
I'll never take this off. That's a promise.

12:18.240 --> 12:22.653
- This'll be my good-luck charm.
- That's right.

12:22.786 --> 12:26.404
Sir? We're ready to move out.
Can I stow your gear?

12:27.624 --> 12:30.162
- We're at war.
- Yo!

12:33.505 --> 12:35.545
Let's go.

12:36.842 --> 12:41.753
When I get back, we're gonna get us
a little condominium right on the beach.

12:41.889 --> 12:43.965
Tell brother Billy to take care.

12:44.099 --> 12:48.227
- And a garage filled up with Porsches.
- Be a good girl. No fooling around.

12:48.353 --> 12:51.604
- Just come back.
- You got it.

12:51.732 --> 12:54.649
Oh. This is Dink. My wife Sally.

12:54.777 --> 12:59.023
Hello, Mrs Hyde. Vi, Captain Hyde's wife.

12:59.156 --> 13:01.195
Hi, Vi.

13:02.618 --> 13:05.025
Be careful.

13:05.162 --> 13:07.914
- You have a spot on your tie.
- What?

13:21.094 --> 13:23.764
Don't wear your skirts so short.

13:50.832 --> 13:52.872
See you around.

14:04.721 --> 14:06.548
- Hey, Vi?
- Yeah?

14:06.682 --> 14:09.967
Do you want a drink?
Can I buy you a drink or something?

14:10.102 --> 14:12.141
Where's open? No place is open.

14:12.271 --> 14:15.770
- Just the Officers Club.
- Any place but there.

14:19.403 --> 14:21.479
Yeah, I guess.

14:22.447 --> 14:25.733
Well... that's that.

14:34.543 --> 14:38.623
Hey. I live just a couple of miles down.
Wanna come over?

14:38.755 --> 14:41.044
- Yeah.
- Stay close.

14:48.765 --> 14:52.099
- Park in there. It's empty.
- OK.

15:01.695 --> 15:05.858
Don't mind the mess. Come on up.

15:17.377 --> 15:19.417
Don't turn it off.

15:43.862 --> 15:45.902
OK?

15:46.031 --> 15:51.701
Yeah. Sorry. Just tonight especially,
I felt superstitious.

15:51.828 --> 15:54.913
Whatever gets you through the night.

15:55.040 --> 15:59.038
- I guess it's the way I was brought up.
- Me too. Is beer OK? It's all I got.

15:59.169 --> 16:01.209
Oh, sure.

16:08.970 --> 16:11.971
You gonna stay on in officers' quarters?

16:12.099 --> 16:15.016
Are you kidding?
I couldn't even if I wanted to.

16:15.143 --> 16:18.393
- That's spooky.
- Bob moves off and I've gotta move.

16:18.522 --> 16:22.519
You're the hole in the doughnut, and
when the doughnut goes, there's no hole.

16:22.651 --> 16:28.404
They say if the Marine Corps wanted you
to have a wife they'd have issued you one.

16:28.532 --> 16:31.201
- Is that you?
- Me and my kid brother.

16:31.326 --> 16:32.951
He's cute.

16:33.078 --> 16:37.407
He inherited the brains,
the beauty, the personality, the talent.

16:37.541 --> 16:39.165
Then he got drafted.

16:39.292 --> 16:41.700
He's the main reason I hang out here.

16:41.837 --> 16:43.876
- Not Dink?
- Dink the kink?

16:45.173 --> 16:51.093
He's part of it. But the kid's
in the VA hospital - psycho ward.

16:51.221 --> 16:55.883
They sent him home without an ignition.
So I'm stuck with him.

16:56.977 --> 17:00.346
God. It must be really hard on you.

17:00.480 --> 17:04.893
I see him every day.
I work in the hospital, in the kitchen.

17:05.026 --> 17:07.814
Is he gonna get better?

17:07.945 --> 17:10.781
Who knows? They don't.

17:10.906 --> 17:12.865
I don't.

17:26.757 --> 17:29.757
- Hey, Pee Wee.
- How are you doing, Mr Martin?

17:29.885 --> 17:33.882
I'm just fine, Pee Wee. Just terrific.
I only stink a <i>little</i> bit.

17:34.014 --> 17:36.968
- Smells like booze to me.
- I need a bath, man.

17:37.100 --> 17:40.185
I just have two hands
and too many assholes to clean.

17:40.312 --> 17:42.351
That's what you're being paid for.

17:42.481 --> 17:45.766
Mr Martin, you get more from Uncle
for your disability

17:45.901 --> 17:48.189
than me and my old lady get put together.

17:48.320 --> 17:51.902
Maybe they shouldn't
put you together, then.

17:52.032 --> 17:55.116
- Your radiator's blowing over.
- So's yours, Eddie.

17:55.243 --> 18:00.404
I'm serious, man. You better watch it
before you pop your melon.

18:00.540 --> 18:04.158
Oh, shit. I'm filled up. Where's Corinne?

18:09.174 --> 18:12.792
You better watch that booze.
Mess up your kidneys.

18:29.653 --> 18:33.318
Watch where you're...! Goddamnit! Shit!

18:33.448 --> 18:36.402
- Oh, shit!
- Oh, my God!

18:38.078 --> 18:41.447
Would you please give me my canes?

18:41.581 --> 18:43.621
I'm sorry.

18:43.750 --> 18:45.790
Goddamnit!

18:47.003 --> 18:54.050
Nurses, interns and orderlies!
Fucking nurses and fucking doctors!

18:54.177 --> 18:57.712
They treat us like nobodies
in this fucking hospital!

18:57.848 --> 19:01.548
- Goddamn it! Where are you people?
- Give it hell, Luke.

19:01.685 --> 19:06.347
Corinne, you're fucking late!
There's something on the floor for you!

19:06.481 --> 19:09.316
You stay where you are, Digroot!

19:09.442 --> 19:14.151
You come near me, I'll break
your fucking head! You understand?

19:14.281 --> 19:17.946
Where the fuck were you? You're
so goddamned slow. Can't you move?

19:18.076 --> 19:22.537
Come near me! I wanna hit you! I wanna
hit something that can't fucking move!

19:22.664 --> 19:24.704
What am I saying?

19:24.833 --> 19:27.288
What am I doing?

19:30.172 --> 19:33.256
- Having a little problem today, Luke?
- Oh, shit!

19:33.383 --> 19:36.004
Doctor, I can't even
get my piss bag changed!

19:36.136 --> 19:39.587
- You want me out of this hospital?
- Give him 50 of Thorazine.

19:39.723 --> 19:45.808
Take care of me and I'll get the fuck
out of here! Just take care of me!

19:47.272 --> 19:52.183
Fucking hospital! Aw, shit!

19:59.576 --> 20:04.368
<i>Put me on a train</i>

20:04.497 --> 20:09.705
<i>I've got no expectations</i>...

20:11.713 --> 20:14.584
- Are you Fleta Wilson?
- Yes.

20:14.716 --> 20:20.635
I think I'd like to volunteer. I mean,
I don't think, I do want to volunteer.

20:20.764 --> 20:22.258
Damn.

20:22.390 --> 20:26.305
Sit down, please.
I'll be with you in a minute.

20:31.149 --> 20:33.189
Hot stuff.

20:47.832 --> 20:50.205
- Do you have him, Jerry?
- Yeah.

20:50.335 --> 20:52.374
One, two, three.

20:58.551 --> 21:02.549
Yeah, I know what you mean.
But you'll get used to it.

21:02.681 --> 21:06.595
One guy had "Born to lose"
tattooed on his arm.

21:06.726 --> 21:09.893
<i>"La vida loca"</i> - the crazy life.
That's my favourite one.

21:10.021 --> 21:12.856
I talked to this other guy
that had a gold earring.

21:12.983 --> 21:17.111
Yeah? You're not used
to those hippy types, huh?

21:17.237 --> 21:21.566
Bob would flip out
if he ever saw those characters.

21:22.450 --> 21:25.451
That about does it, huh?

21:25.578 --> 21:30.287
I feel like I've lived in base houses
all my life.

21:32.877 --> 21:34.953
Should've had the government move us.

21:35.088 --> 21:38.539
- They do that for officers, you know?
- Yeah?

21:38.675 --> 21:42.423
I didn't realise that we'd accumulated
so much stuff.

21:42.554 --> 21:46.219
Well, don't worry. My rates are cheap.

21:47.767 --> 21:52.762
You know, I think I must have moved
at least 15 times since I left home.

21:52.897 --> 21:57.440
I went back there once
when my old lady died.

21:57.569 --> 22:02.112
Nothing's left. They tore down my past
and built a shopping centre.

22:02.240 --> 22:05.407
- Want to see something funny?
- I'd love to.

22:05.535 --> 22:07.575
My yearbook.

22:10.707 --> 22:13.827
- Ooh! Look at that dress.
- It was a nice dress.

22:13.960 --> 22:16.166
- It's cute.
- There's another one here.

22:16.296 --> 22:18.668
So funny looking at
the way we used to look.

22:18.798 --> 22:22.048
- Doggy in the window?
- Look.

22:24.012 --> 22:27.345
"Sally Bender. Nickname: Sal."

22:28.683 --> 22:32.515
"What is the one thing
she'd want on a desert island?"

22:32.645 --> 22:34.852
"A husband."

22:34.981 --> 22:38.682
- I was so ambitious.
- And so original.

22:38.818 --> 22:42.686
You know that guy we were talking about?
He's in here somewhere.

22:42.822 --> 22:45.064
- Yeah?
- Look.

22:45.200 --> 22:47.773
"Luke Martin. Nickname: The Duke."

22:47.911 --> 22:51.196
- He's cute.
- "Co-captain of the football team."

22:51.331 --> 22:55.744
"What one thing would he want
on a desert island? A mirror."

22:55.877 --> 23:00.586
- This is asinine, Pee Wee.
- There you go. Take some.

23:00.715 --> 23:04.962
Don't you get the feeling
that this is kinda silly shit?

23:13.144 --> 23:17.890
Shit, I'm not saying
this isn't entertaining, Pee Wee.

23:19.651 --> 23:23.067
I'm not eating, Pee Wee. I'm not eating.

23:24.572 --> 23:27.776
I'm not eating, Pee Wee. Come on, man.

23:27.909 --> 23:32.785
Give me my arms. I can feed myself.
This is bullshit. I'm not a child, man.

23:32.914 --> 23:34.954
Drink the milk.

23:48.388 --> 23:51.472
- Hi there.
- Hello.

24:00.358 --> 24:02.398
Juice and coffee!

24:03.361 --> 24:05.401
Want some juice?

24:08.324 --> 24:11.409
Excuse me. Do you want
some juice or coffee?

