- Juice or coffee?
- Look at that round-eyed chick!

24:15.748 --> 24:17.788
Come on, baby, light my fire.

24:19.419 --> 24:23.582
- Wanna boom-boom? Short time?
- Like some juice?

24:23.715 --> 24:26.502
I'm hard all over.
I'm a bargain in this ward.

24:26.634 --> 24:30.086
Hey, man, be cool. I told you.
Get yourself together.

24:30.221 --> 24:35.346
- Do you want some juice?
- Tits... ass... You got it all, Mama-san.

24:35.476 --> 24:38.181
- You got it all.
- Hey, you shut up.

24:38.313 --> 24:43.817
Yes, sir. Right away. You hear that?
You're disturbing these young 'uns.

24:43.943 --> 24:47.395
Can I kiss you? Can I sniff? Oh, man.

24:50.950 --> 24:52.990
Luke?

24:54.913 --> 24:56.952
Can I come in?

24:59.959 --> 25:02.201
How are you doing?

25:08.051 --> 25:12.048
- Do you remember me?
- No.

25:12.180 --> 25:14.671
I was at Lincoln High
when you were there.

25:14.807 --> 25:19.766
Sally Hyde. Well, I was Sally Bender
when... when I was there.

25:21.773 --> 25:23.812
So?

25:28.321 --> 25:30.693
I just started volunteering today here.

25:30.823 --> 25:34.868
Terrific. If I could get my hands loose,
I'd salute you.

25:41.000 --> 25:43.040
You're a mess.

25:46.047 --> 25:48.620
- Sally Bender.
- Right.

25:50.426 --> 25:55.088
- You were a cheerleader.
- That's right. Three years.

26:00.853 --> 26:04.139
- Were you wounded in 'Nam?
- Right.

26:04.274 --> 26:06.978
When did it happen?

26:08.987 --> 26:11.026
A long time ago.

26:13.825 --> 26:18.368
- My husband just went over there.
- Poor bastard.

26:31.426 --> 26:33.465
Sally?

26:34.721 --> 26:38.339
Didn't we used to call you Bender Over?

26:38.474 --> 26:42.686
- What? Who said that?
- Bender Over. Everybody said it.

26:42.812 --> 26:45.813
- They did not!
- Yes, they did, Sally.

26:45.940 --> 26:49.689
Oh, come on. They did not.
What are you talking about?

26:49.819 --> 26:51.859
Oh, shit.

26:51.988 --> 26:55.155
Sally, listen.
Can I ask you for a big favour?

26:55.283 --> 26:57.322
Sure.

26:57.452 --> 27:01.532
How about unhitching me
from these things?

27:02.832 --> 27:05.916
- No, I can't do that, Luke.
- Sure you can. It's easy.

27:06.044 --> 27:09.993
No, I'm sorry. The doctor
has to do that. I...

27:10.131 --> 27:13.547
Come on. Please? Please, Sally Bender.

27:18.639 --> 27:20.928
- Come on.
- What are you doing in here?

27:21.059 --> 27:24.262
- I just was seeing...
- We'll tend to Mr Martin, Sally.

27:24.395 --> 27:27.182
- You're needed on the ward.
- OK.

27:28.941 --> 27:33.153
Hey, Bender.
You almost got yourself a gold star.

27:41.454 --> 27:43.696
Pee Wee, I can crawl again.

27:52.006 --> 27:54.046
Morning.

27:55.677 --> 28:01.382
I'm gonna be feeding you this morning.
I'm a new volunteer here.

28:01.516 --> 28:03.555
Huh?

28:06.604 --> 28:12.191
He ain't transistorised, honey.
You gotta plug him in for sound.

28:12.318 --> 28:14.358
Plug you in? Oh.

28:19.450 --> 28:22.321
Is this... is this gonna hurt?

28:25.832 --> 28:28.038
There. Is that OK?

28:29.252 --> 28:32.668
- Thank you.
- OK. Would you like some food?

28:33.756 --> 28:36.591
Hey, there you go. Oh, my.

28:36.717 --> 28:38.757
- I'm sorry.
- That's OK.

28:38.886 --> 28:40.926
You want me to...? Here.

28:41.055 --> 28:43.095
Here. Here you go.

28:45.685 --> 28:48.555
It's all energy. You understand?

28:49.772 --> 28:53.224
You don't understand.
You give out energy, you get energy back.

28:53.359 --> 28:57.191
You see me smiling?
Can you dig them pearly whites?

28:57.321 --> 29:00.239
I smile my ass off now.

29:00.366 --> 29:04.494
Hell, sometimes I think
I'm the Good Humor Man.

29:04.620 --> 29:08.748
Everyone wants a piece of my action.
They think I'm one of the Beach Boys.

29:08.875 --> 29:13.335
- Hey, Sally. This is my brother, Bill.
- Hi, Bill.

29:15.339 --> 29:19.882
You see that? Me and her just had
a whole conversation in smile contact.

29:20.011 --> 29:24.305
- Vi, do you have a jumper cable?
- Sure. Bridges!

29:24.432 --> 29:26.471
Watch. You watching?

29:30.730 --> 29:33.980
You two just did it. You smiled
"See what I have to put up with?"

29:34.108 --> 29:36.148
And she smiled back "He's harmless."

29:36.277 --> 29:38.483
- Are you on uppers?
- I don't know.

29:38.613 --> 29:42.029
Come on, Bill.
How about a game of chess?

29:44.243 --> 29:47.861
My brother -
a miracle of modern medicine.

29:51.250 --> 29:56.327
Hey, wait. Oh, my God, what a day.
Is he usually like that?

30:03.763 --> 30:05.174
Try it!

30:08.059 --> 30:10.098
Is it charging?

30:14.815 --> 30:16.689
No.

30:16.817 --> 30:21.776
I like this one.
This is beautiful. It's a convertible.

30:23.032 --> 30:29.781
I don't know how you'd keep warm.
Oh, it's got a great sound system.

30:29.914 --> 30:31.112
Hello.

30:31.249 --> 30:35.163
- Why is this one so much less expensive?
- It's two years older.

30:35.294 --> 30:41.463
"I'm so tired when I come home at night,
I just fall right asleep."

30:41.592 --> 30:44.427
"I know you didn't want me
to get a job..." Thanks.

30:44.554 --> 30:51.600
"...but this isn't really a job, since
I don't get paid. I hope you don't mind."

30:51.727 --> 30:56.639
Then there's sort of a sexy ending.
"Love, Sally."

30:56.774 --> 30:59.443
- That's nice.
- Thanks.

31:01.821 --> 31:06.483
But you didn't tell him the house
you rented was on the beach.

31:06.617 --> 31:08.491
I know.

31:09.537 --> 31:13.237
And you didn't tell him
about the new car you bought.

31:13.374 --> 31:17.123
I figure I'm gonna save that
for when he gets home.

31:19.422 --> 31:23.254
- I got one from Dink this morning.
- Oh, yeah?

31:23.384 --> 31:28.461
All he said was "Got you another ear."
Poetic, huh?

31:29.765 --> 31:35.352
A captain? Shit, Bender. You didn't
go out and marry a fucking captain?

31:35.479 --> 31:38.813
That's right. Why? What were you?

31:38.941 --> 31:40.981
A sergeant.

31:41.110 --> 31:44.313
Sergeants have a lot
of responsibility, don't they?

31:44.447 --> 31:47.448
Yes. They sent me my stripes
on the hospital ship.

31:47.575 --> 31:50.576
My reward for getting so fucked up!

31:51.412 --> 31:54.828
Why are you so cynical about that, Luke?

31:56.292 --> 31:59.827
What are you doing here, Bender?
Why aren't you on a golf course?

31:59.962 --> 32:02.749
Doing something you're good at.

32:02.882 --> 32:04.921
I'm just trying to keep busy.

32:05.051 --> 32:07.506
Sure. Something
to talk about over martinis.

32:07.637 --> 32:10.922
How you're helping out the poor cripples.

32:13.142 --> 32:16.593
I don't think that
I deserve that, Luke - at all.

32:16.729 --> 32:21.687
Maybe you're getting ready for your
husband to come back in a body bag.

32:28.199 --> 32:30.026
Read someplace else!

32:32.745 --> 32:34.784
Luke?

32:34.997 --> 32:37.037
Luke.

32:40.419 --> 32:42.745
Stop! Stop and listen to me!

32:45.800 --> 32:48.172
What is the matter with you?

32:52.682 --> 32:55.386
Why do you have to be such a bastard?

33:08.864 --> 33:12.814
Kevin. I thought
you died Wednesday, man.

33:12.952 --> 33:17.495
You can get paralysed in a war
that don't even make sense

33:17.623 --> 33:21.952
and come back and they don't have
the decency to ask you how you're doing.

33:22.086 --> 33:24.209
"Can I do anything for you?"

33:24.338 --> 33:29.629
I got a Purple Heart. I got it from a second
lieutenant that wasn't even in the war.

33:29.760 --> 33:32.845
They don't tell you about
how to manage your finances.

33:32.972 --> 33:37.301
Or going back into society. Half
the people still can't go back into society.

33:37.435 --> 33:41.135
What about your sex life?
They don't tell you about that.

33:41.272 --> 33:44.059
I went out the first time
and didn't know what to do.

33:44.191 --> 33:48.770
What happens if my gizmo busts? What
happens if I have a bowel movement?

33:48.904 --> 33:51.360
I get there and I don't know how to react.

33:52.241 --> 33:55.028
There's not enough beds,
not enough staff.

33:55.161 --> 33:58.031
It's really crowded.
The guys have to wait in line.

33:58.164 --> 34:01.663
They're not prepared for the number
of wounded being sent back.

34:01.792 --> 34:05.292
I don't think we're clear
on what you're asking us for, Sally.

34:07.173 --> 34:12.629
It's what I said. We could do an article
in the paper, using these photographs,

34:12.762 --> 34:15.217
interviewing some of the guys, maybe.

34:15.347 --> 34:18.099
Isn't it difficult for the men
to be around women?

34:18.225 --> 34:21.594
When I joined Weight Watchers
I didn't want candy in the house.

34:21.728 --> 34:24.136
I don't think that's our function, Sally.

34:24.273 --> 34:28.022
We're more a base gossip sheet.
Fun and games for the fellas.

34:28.152 --> 34:32.813
I agree with you, Connie.
I'm sorry, Sally. I hope you understand.

34:32.947 --> 34:36.697
What's next in the agenda?

34:36.827 --> 34:42.201
We have the Little League play-offs
and the officer-son baseball game.

34:42.333 --> 34:45.868
That's the 25th and the 27th, isn't it?

34:46.003 --> 34:49.123
I just... I want to say
that I'm really shocked

34:49.255 --> 34:53.503
that you'd rather write about
a goddamn home run than this hospital.

34:53.636 --> 34:57.550
- Sally, please.
- What if they were your husbands?

35:04.271 --> 35:07.142
<i>That sure is a mindblower!</i>

35:07.274 --> 35:10.026
<i>That's the way it was done 150 years ago</i>.

35:10.152 --> 35:14.197
- <i>Things have improved</i>.
- <i>They certainly have</i>.

35:14.323 --> 35:20.741
<i>Picture a young man 150 years ago</i>
<i>in the beautiful hills of Kentucky</i>.

35:20.871 --> 35:24.205
<i>There's a girl he's crazy about</i>.
<i>She's lovely, vivacious</i>...

35:24.333 --> 35:26.824
What's shaking, man?

35:26.961 --> 35:32.335
One of them days, man.
Flashback to when I got fucked up.

35:34.969 --> 35:37.008
<i>Wow!</i>

35:38.180 --> 35:41.430
<i>Get out of the way!</i>

35:53.445 --> 35:58.107
<i>Nobody feels any pain</i>

35:59.952 --> 36:04.329
<i>Tonight as I stand inside the rain</i>

36:06.333 --> 36:09.168
<i>Everybody knows</i>

36:09.295 --> 36:12.379
<i>That baby's got new clothes</i>...

36:14.008 --> 36:21.635
<i>He dedicated himself to justice and</i>
<i>love between his fellow human beings</i>.

36:23.934 --> 36:26.223
<i>He gave his life for that principle</i>

36:26.353 --> 36:30.896
<i>and I think it's up to those of us</i>
<i>who are here</i>...

36:35.029 --> 36:39.358
It was a choice between dealing with that
or dealing with this football game

36:39.491 --> 36:42.991
and they just said it's not our function.

36:43.120 --> 36:45.528
Maybe I'm naive.

36:47.082 --> 36:49.870
Naive? She wants to know if she's naive!

36:50.002 --> 36:52.707
- Oh, man. That's cold.
- I'm a cold man.

36:52.838 --> 36:55.709
It's like you've done your duty,
served your purpose,

36:55.841 --> 36:59.506
so they just toss you into the heap
like a used Kleenex.

36:59.637 --> 37:01.676
That's the way it is. That's it.

37:01.805 --> 37:06.598
What is our function if it isn't to deal with
the problems you guys face every day?

37:06.727 --> 37:09.763
God! The smugness just...
I can't believe it.

37:09.897 --> 37:12.851
- Give 'em hell, Bender.
- Sorry.

37:12.983 --> 37:16.399
It's not gonna do any good,
but I'm rooting for you.

37:16.528 --> 37:19.316
Well, thanks a lot, Luke.

37:19.448 --> 37:22.235
Seriously, if they put
something in the paper...

37:22.368 --> 37:25.701
You're beautiful when you're excited.

37:28.582 --> 37:33.244
<i>Yes, I believe it's time for us to quit</i>

37:35.089 --> 37:38.090
<i>When we meet again</i>

37:38.217 --> 37:41.301
<i>Introduced as friends</i>

37:41.428 --> 37:47.099
<i>Please don't let on</i>
<i>that you knew me when</i>

37:47.226 --> 37:52.469
<i>I was hungry and it was your worid</i>

37:52.606 --> 37:56.651
<i>Ah, you fake just like a woman</i>...

37:56.777 --> 38:01.024
God only knows
what he saw over there... or did.

38:03.325 --> 38:08.071
I don't understand it.
He was only in 'Nam for two weeks.

38:08.205 --> 38:11.241
I worry a lot about Dink too.

38:11.375 --> 38:15.538
He's so funny, you know?
So uncomplicated.

38:15.671 --> 38:18.244
He's more than just a roll in the sack.

38:20.092 --> 38:23.176
I just hope he doesn't get totalled.

38:28.225 --> 38:31.559
Whoo!

38:36.400 --> 38:38.439
I got it.

38:41.363 --> 38:44.649
- Bender!
- You got a chair!

38:44.783 --> 38:48.484
- You changed your hair!
- You like it?

38:48.620 --> 38:52.155
- Yeah. It's very nice.
- You're mobile.

38:52.291 --> 38:54.414
- I'll help you. Go ahead.
- Thanks, Luke.

38:54.543 --> 38:56.583
- Hi, Rick.
- Hey, Luke. How you doing?

38:56.712 --> 38:58.751
Congratulations.

39:11.769 --> 39:14.438
Would you like to come over for dinner?

39:14.563 --> 39:17.647
Wouldn't you like to
get out of here one night?

39:17.775 --> 39:19.814
I'm a good cook.

39:22.071 --> 39:24.110
OK?

39:25.240 --> 39:29.570
<i>("Jumping Jack Flash"</i>
<i>by the Rolling Stones}</i>

39:38.587 --> 39:40.627
<i>Watch it</i>

39:45.803 --> 39:50.299
<i>I was born in a crossfire hurricane</i>

39:52.392 --> 39:57.138
<i>And I howled at my ma</i>
<i>in the driving rain</i>...

40:17.960 --> 40:21.329
I hit him after the whistle, man!

40:21.463 --> 40:26.421
It was wrong! He grabbed my chair!
Didn't you grab my chair?

40:39.314 --> 40:43.229
Can't you morons kick a field goal?
Come on! Field goal!

40:46.613 --> 40:50.658
B- u-s-t! Bust 'em!

41:07.551 --> 41:11.880
And around about July 1st,
my pa's mind would start wandering.

41:12.014 --> 41:17.256
He wouldn't give a damn about the cattle,
and that got us kids pretty excited.

41:17.394 --> 41:20.348
At the park they'd have flags flying
and games of chance,

41:20.481 --> 41:23.018
kissing booths and wrestling matches.

41:23.150 --> 41:27.444
But let me tell you,
that day was always too long for me.

41:27.571 --> 41:31.699
When it got dark, the band
would play "The Star-Spangled Banner"

41:31.825 --> 41:33.865
and the fireworks would start up,

41:33.994 --> 41:38.490
and I'd start thinking how brave those
men were that fought in the Revolution.

41:38.624 --> 41:43.036
I'd dream about those men,
how they went to war for our freedom.

41:43.170 --> 41:46.040
I guess that's when I decided
to be a soldier,

41:46.173 --> 41:49.423
seeing the sky lit up with those rockets.

41:49.551 --> 41:51.591
I enlisted when I became of age.

41:51.720 --> 41:54.389
I served in Europe and Worid War Two

41:54.514 --> 41:58.049
and was involved in the liberation
of dozens of towns.

41:58.185 --> 42:02.183
As I passed through them,
as I saw the faces of the people,

42:02.314 --> 42:05.932
I realised I had fulfilled my dream.

42:06.068 --> 42:11.109
I had become one of those men
who had gone to war for freedom.

42:11.240 --> 42:14.157
I sure wound up doing
what I wanted to do,

42:14.284 --> 42:17.902
and that's what July 4th means to me.

42:26.880 --> 42:30.545
- I bet you can't do that.
- I can't do that. Can you do this?

42:33.387 --> 42:36.174
- No.
- Go on, try it.

42:38.475 --> 42:40.515
I can't do it.

42:40.644 --> 42:45.270
Hey, Billy the Kid. Let's show
these guys what real talent is. Come on.

42:45.399 --> 42:49.348
Give me your arm. You know,
the duet we worked up last night.

42:53.907 --> 42:58.320
- Billy, you gonna play that thing?
- Come on, Billy. Play your guitar.

42:58.453 --> 43:01.988
Come on. I love
when you play the guitar.

43:17.014 --> 43:22.435
What is tomorrow? What is it we need?

43:22.561 --> 43:25.431
What will it give us?

43:25.564 --> 43:27.936
A new life we can lead

43:28.066 --> 43:33.690
Will the wind crack the limbs
of a few dying trees?

43:37.200 --> 43:42.824
Will the branches unite
and bend in the breeze?

43:43.915 --> 43:48.577
Tomorrow is hope
for it is something I've not seen

43:49.713 --> 43:56.166
Tomorrow is a sunny day...
live in a sunny dream...

44:07.064 --> 44:10.148
Come on, Billy. That sounded great.

44:20.160 --> 44:22.200
Shit.

44:24.539 --> 44:27.659
I can't play my fucking guitar.

44:44.935 --> 44:47.177
God!

44:53.527 --> 44:55.899
It's all right, man.

44:57.239 --> 44:59.362
It's gonna be all right.

45:02.869 --> 45:07.827
I think it really helped him
having you there. I really do.

45:13.171 --> 45:15.413
Luke, are you OK?

45:16.967 --> 45:21.130
- Yeah.
- Should we do the dinner another night?

45:21.263 --> 45:23.302
No. No.

45:50.792 --> 45:54.576
I think you were really wonderful
with him. I really do.

46:06.767 --> 46:09.720
Oh, boy.

46:09.853 --> 46:13.685
Just come down here
and hold the chair for me.

46:16.151 --> 46:18.309
Thanks.

46:28.246 --> 46:30.618
You could pick my ankles up.

46:39.508 --> 46:42.508
Thank you. That's good. Thank you.

46:44.554 --> 46:46.594
It's warm because I've had the oven on.

46:46.723 --> 46:52.477
I've got one of those timing devices
that cooks your food while you're at work.

46:52.604 --> 46:54.643
Whoo.

46:56.399 --> 46:59.733
Let me just move you around a bit.

46:59.861 --> 47:02.732
- You like margaritas?
- Yeah.

47:02.864 --> 47:05.402
Well...

47:05.534 --> 47:08.653
I just happen to have some.

47:12.332 --> 47:14.621
Let me just...

47:18.421 --> 47:21.173
Do you get a chance to go out very much?

47:21.299 --> 47:24.917
- Do you go to people's homes?
- No, I don't.

47:31.184 --> 47:33.556
Let's go in the living room.

47:35.564 --> 47:37.936
I think you can make it. OK?

47:51.746 --> 47:53.822
Let's see. Um...

47:56.668 --> 47:59.373
Wait a minute. What am I doing?

47:59.504 --> 48:03.003
- What?
- What am I lighting a fire for?

48:04.384 --> 48:06.460
It's the old Girl Scout instinct.

48:06.595 --> 48:08.634
Let's see. I've got a dip...

48:11.683 --> 48:14.470
Sit down, Bender.

48:14.603 --> 48:16.642
Sit down.

48:20.567 --> 48:23.354
- Are you nervous?
-

48:23.486 --> 48:25.526
Yes.

48:27.616 --> 48:29.655
Why are you nervous?

48:32.329 --> 48:35.911
This isn't "Have a Gimp Over
for Dinner" Night, is it?

48:36.041 --> 48:38.828
You're not one of those weirdos?

48:43.214 --> 48:45.884
No, I'm not, Luke.

48:48.887 --> 48:50.926
I know you're not.

48:53.892 --> 48:58.055
I'm just very happy to be here.

49:04.611 --> 49:06.900
I'm glad you're here.

49:12.911 --> 49:15.069
How about some music?

49:16.498 --> 49:18.537
Well...

49:19.626 --> 49:23.955
I don't think you're gonna
like my records very much.

49:24.089 --> 49:26.959
You probably won't
like the way I dance either.

49:30.095 --> 49:33.049
Well...

49:35.350 --> 49:39.976
Do you know that when I dream,
I'm not in the chair?

49:40.105 --> 49:44.268
I don't even have a chair in my dream.
I have legs.

49:47.404 --> 49:52.315
When I was a kid, I used to jump
in my mother's kitchen

49:52.450 --> 49:54.988
and touch the ceiling.

49:55.120 --> 50:01.324
She used to get pissed off cos
I'd leave my handprints on the ceiling.

50:01.459 --> 50:05.327
I still check the snow reports,
the conditions at Mammoth.

50:05.463 --> 50:08.250
I'm still the same person, you know.

50:09.342 --> 50:12.711
It's funny.
When people look at me, they see...

50:12.846 --> 50:16.594
something else,
but they don't see who I am.

50:20.145 --> 50:24.605
I think people have a real hard time
seeing who other people really are.

50:24.733 --> 50:28.267
People don't see <i>me</i> like I really am.

50:28.403 --> 50:35.402
People look at me, I think, and they see
"Oh, cheery Sally, the captain's wife."

50:42.125 --> 50:47.166
Sometimes I feel like
